cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY 

This paper is primarily focused on the complexity of deep neural networks (DNN) and their ability to represent piecewise linear (PWL) functions. This topic is closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of DNNs in computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY), which further supports these sub-categories. Finally, the paper also includes empirical results and computational methods, which suggest that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a likely sub-category as well.
